.SH "NAME"
kstat_irqs_usr \- Get the statistics for an interrupt
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'unsigned\ int\ kstat_irqs_usr('u
.BI "unsigned int kstat_irqs_usr(unsigned\ int\ " "irq" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIirq\fR
.RS 4
The interrupt number
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Returns the sum of interrupt counts on all cpus since boot for
\fIirq\fR\&. Contrary to
\fBkstat_irqs\fR
this can be called from any preemptible context\&. It\*(Aqs protected against concurrent removal of an interrupt descriptor when sparse irqs are enabled\&.
